				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">An even more stealth way to use the stack is to push bytes on the bottom of the stack to reserve space at reset (or simply TXS a value lower than $FF). The lets you use some space, say $1F0-1FF, and the chances of it interfering are extremely improbable. The Powerpak NSF player does this, since some rare NSFs still use the low area of $100 for things, but none depend on the reset state of the stack (this would be forbidden by the NSF spec anyway).</div>

