				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Right now your NSF uses short arrays in RAM spaced all over it every 64 or 128 bytes, all the way from $0200 up to $07FF. It's hard to be sure what exactly that MML replay engine is doing, and whether they'll actually use all that space (in which case, no sprites for you) or are just pretending to be a gas (and expanding to fill all available space; in this case you could move things around to make space).<br /><br />You should probably talk to the developer and ask what's going on, and if they might be willing to make a version that leaves 256 contiguous bytes for you somewhere.</div>

