						<div class="postbody">To do what rainwarrior suggests, look for sounddrv.h in the MML package. (provided whatever I downloaded is actually what you mentioned)<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;.memclear<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0000,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0200,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0300,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0400,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0500,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0600,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0700,x<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;inx<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;bne&nbsp; &nbsp;.memclear<br /><br /></div><br />to<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">;&nbsp; &nbsp;.memclear<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0000,x<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0200,x<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0300,x<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0400,x<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0500,x<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0600,x<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sta&nbsp; &nbsp;$0700,x<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;inx<br />;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;bne&nbsp; &nbsp;.memclear<br /></div><br /><br />Also, the screen won't cause any problems, just take out the semicolon before JSR DrawScreen  on line 131. Instead of sprites, the background could be updated for a cursor, but that requires a bit more work. Also, if you want more than 10 songs (or as many will fit on the screen if you change it), that also becomes more work.</div>

